when I have you to protect me?

00:12:31.235 --> 00:12:33.504 position:35% line:89% align:start
Nagisa...

00:12:33.504 --> 00:12:36.973 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Tomoya]ÚEven though she said
that... everything had changed.

00:12:36.973 --> 00:12:40.342 position:19% line:83% align:start
@I couldn't pretend to
beúas happy as I was before.

00:12:49.715 --> 00:12:51.618 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Sanae]: Tomoya.

00:12:51.618 --> 00:12:54.553 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh. Hey, Sanae.

00:12:54.553 --> 00:12:56.387 position:19% line:89% align:start
So, how was your day?

00:12:56.387 --> 00:12:59.456 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Sanae]: This is where
Nagisa used to work? I see!

00:12:59.456 --> 00:13:02.124 position:7% line:83% align:start
I always wanted to come here,
but never found the time.

00:13:02.124 --> 00:13:03.492 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's a pretty groovy
place, isn't it?

00:13:03.492 --> 00:13:05.394 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're slang's a little off.

00:13:05.394 --> 00:13:08.329 position:13% line:83% align:start
Huh? Well, now I feel old.
[slight chuckle]

00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:17.336 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's something I need
to talk to you about.

00:13:17.336 --> 00:13:19.538 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah?

00:13:19.538 --> 00:13:22.306 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's about Nagisa and the baby.

00:13:22.306 --> 00:13:24.208 position:16% line:83% align:start
I spoke with her doctor
the other day

00:13:24.208 --> 00:13:26.544 position:7% line:83% align:start
and he said there may be some
risks we didn't know about

00:13:26.544 --> 00:13:28.444 position:19% line:89% align:start
when she gives birth.

00:13:28.444 --> 00:13:31.346 position:16% line:83% align:start
And just for the record,
I haven't told Nagisa yet.

00:13:31.346 --> 00:13:34.282 position:7% line:83% align:start
The doctor told me in private,
but you should know, too.

00:13:37.351 --> 00:13:41.188 position:10% line:83% align:start
You say some risks, but what
exactly do you mean by that?

00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:44.722 position:21% line:83% align:start
Are you saying that
Nagisa might die?

00:13:44.722 --> 00:13:47.959 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm not sure; They said the
burden placed on her body

00:13:47.959 --> 00:13:50.027 position:16% line:83% align:start
will be a little greater
than a normal delivery.

00:13:50.027 --> 00:13:51.528 position:5% line:89% align:start
But that's speaking for Nagisa,

00:13:51.528 --> 00:13:54.163 position:19% line:83% align:start
the childbirth itself
should be unaffected.

00:13:54.163 --> 00:13:55.598 position:38% line:89% align:start
I see...

00:13:55.598 --> 00:13:57.832 position:13% line:83% align:start
Of course, that's assuming
Nagisa' health stays stable

00:13:57.832 --> 00:13:59.301 position:24% line:89% align:start
for the delivery.

00:13:59.301 --> 00:14:01.936 position:13% line:83% align:start
As you know, her condition
gets worse sometimes.

00:14:01.936 --> 00:14:04.438 position:16% line:83% align:start
That could be a serious
factor in this as well.

00:14:04.438 --> 00:14:06.839 position:10% line:83% align:start
To be honest, we don't know
much about Nagisa's illness,

00:14:06.839 --> 00:14:08.774 position:16% line:89% align:start
so it's hard to predict.

00:14:08.774 --> 00:14:11.276 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Sanae]: I think the doctor was
worried about a worst-case
scenario,

00:14:11.276 --> 00:14:13.311 position:19% line:83% align:start
but we should be ready
for anything.

00:14:14.679 --> 00:14:16.581 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's hard to say
what's the right choice

00:14:16.581 --> 00:14:19.049 position:10% line:83% align:start
and what's the wrong choice
in this situation.

00:14:19.049 --> 00:14:21.383 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's why I wanted to go
over things with you first;

00:14:21.383 --> 00:14:23.385 position:13% line:83% align:start
So you could give it some
careful consideration.

00:14:23.385 --> 00:14:26.254 position:16% line:83% align:start
Take some time and talk
to Nagisa about it.

00:14:26.254 --> 00:14:27.821 position:19% line:83% align:start
Once you've discussed
the situation,

00:14:27.821 --> 00:14:30.123 position:27% line:83% align:start
you can talk to
the doctor together.

00:14:30.123 --> 00:14:33.326 position:5% line:83% align:start
Then we can all make a decision
together as a family.

00:14:34.894 --> 00:14:37.429 position:27% line:83% align:start
Considering the
worst-case scenario...

00:14:37.429 --> 00:14:41.265 position:7% line:83% align:start
do you think we should give up
on having a baby, now?

00:14:41.265 --> 00:14:43.900 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm afraid that isn't
my place to say.

00:14:46.236 --> 00:14:48.438 position:5% line:89% align:start
However... if you go that route,

00:14:48.438 --> 00:14:52.139 position:21% line:83% align:start
you should do it as
quickly as you can.

00:14:52.139 --> 00:14:54.108 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Sanae]: I want you two to
really think about this.

00:14:54.108 --> 00:14:56.109 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Tomoya]: Thanks for caring
for us so much, Sanae.

00:14:56.109 --> 00:14:57.911 position:19% line:89% align:start
It really means a lot.

00:14:57.911 --> 00:14:59.945 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're a family, after all.

00:15:03.282 --> 00:15:06.084 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry. I still
want to have the baby.

00:15:06.084 --> 00:15:08.385 position:19% line:83% align:start
No, it's fine; I had a
feeling you'd say that.

00:15:08.385 --> 00:15:11.154 position:16% line:83% align:start
I know I'm weak and this
could be a risk for me...

00:15:11.154 --> 00:15:13.489 position:16% line:83% align:start
but I don't want to rob
my child of a chance at life

00:15:13.489 --> 00:15:15.123 position:27% line:89% align:start
because of that.

00:15:15.123 --> 00:15:17.292 position:13% line:83% align:start
So if it's safer to have a
delivery at the hospital...

00:15:17.292 --> 00:15:20.595 position:10% line:83% align:start
then I don't mind giving up
on the home birth.

00:15:20.595 --> 00:15:23.029 position:35% line:89% align:start
Nagisa...

00:15:23.029 --> 00:15:26.466 position:16% line:83% align:start
Tomoya... I want to see
our child, no matter what.

00:15:29.101 --> 00:15:31.336 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Akio]:
So, what did the doctor say?

00:15:31.336 --> 00:15:33.037 position:24% line:83% align:start
He said she would
have fewer risks

00:15:33.037 --> 00:15:35.038 position:24% line:83% align:start
if she gave birth
at the hospital.

00:15:35.038 --> 00:15:37.873 position:16% line:83% align:start
I guess that's a relief,
but I'm still worried about it.

00:15:37.873 --> 00:15:41.277 position:5% line:83% align:start
I take it Nagisa hasn't changed
her mind on the issue, then?

00:15:41.277 --> 00:15:43.778 position:44% line:89% align:start
No.

00:15:43.778 --> 00:15:47.381 position:7% line:77% align:start
[Tomoya]ÚI think she's pretty
scared@about this whole thing,
though.

00:15:47.381 --> 00:15:49.316 position:27% line:83% align:start
She tries to act
like she's happy,

00:15:49.316 --> 00:15:52.151 position:19% line:83% align:start
but she probably feels
the same way I do.

00:16:00.790 --> 00:16:03.259 position:16% line:89% align:start
All right. Come with me.

00:16:15.101 --> 00:16:18.638 position:7% line:83% align:start
Here you go, my secret hideout
in all its glory.

00:16:18.638 --> 00:16:20.439 position:10% line:83% align:start
I come here to play baseball
with the kids...

00:16:20.439 --> 00:16:23.207 position:24% line:83% align:start
or just space out
and spend some time alone.

00:16:23.207 --> 00:16:25.976 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Tomoya]: I get it. So all those
times you disappeared from work,

00:16:25.976 --> 00:16:28.145 position:16% line:83% align:start
this is where you came.
Not quite what I expected.

00:16:28.145 --> 00:16:31.013 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Akio]: They've been cutting
down the trees bit by bit.

00:16:31.013 --> 00:16:32.281 position:21% line:89% align:start
Sooner or later...,

00:16:32.281 --> 00:16:34.983 position:21% line:83% align:start
They're gonna build
a hospital here.

00:16:34.983 --> 00:16:37.185 position:7% line:89% align:start
Anyway, that's not the point.

00:16:40.254 --> 00:16:44.057 position:19% line:83% align:start
Remember that story I
told you two years ago?

00:16:44.057 --> 00:16:46.191 position:24% line:83% align:start
When I was in the
theater troupe, I mean.

00:16:46.191 --> 00:16:50.328 position:7% line:83% align:start
Back when Sanae was a teacher,
before we had the bakery.

00:16:50.328 --> 00:16:54.665 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Akio]: Like I told you before,
Nagisa ended up staying by
herself

00:16:54.665 --> 00:16:57.933 position:16% line:83% align:start
a lot during that time.
On that particular day,

00:16:57.933 --> 00:17:01.102 position:7% line:83% align:start
Sanae had to go to work and we
ended up leaving Nagisa home

00:17:01.102 --> 00:17:02.370 position:30% line:89% align:start
with a fever.

00:17:02.370 --> 00:17:04.072 position:21% line:83% align:start
Of course, we tried
to get off work,

00:17:04.072 --> 00:17:07.507 position:10% line:89% align:start
but it just didn't work out.

00:17:07.507 --> 00:17:09.710 position:13% line:83% align:start
When we left her, Nagisa's
condition was stable,

00:17:09.710 --> 00:17:13.912 position:13% line:83% align:start
so we hoped we'd get back
before anything bad happened.

00:17:13.912 --> 00:17:15.913 position:30% line:83% align:start
Unfortunately,
Nagisa went outside,

00:17:15.913 --> 00:17:17.816 position:10% line:89% align:start
waiting for us to come home.

00:17:17.816 --> 00:17:20.317 position:13% line:83% align:start
We found her collapsed in
the snow when we came back.

00:17:20.317 --> 00:17:22.518 position:21% line:83% align:start
By dawn, things were
looking pretty grim.

00:17:22.518 --> 00:17:26.154 position:10% line:83% align:start
I didn't even know that kind
of sadness was possible.

00:17:27.122 --> 00:17:28.423 position:7% line:89% align:start
What I'm about to tell you now

00:17:28.423 --> 00:17:31.392 position:27% line:83% align:start
I've never told
anyone but Sanae.

00:17:31.392 --> 00:17:33.761 position:24% line:83% align:start
Before I knew it,
I was running and running

00:17:33.761 --> 00:17:36.229 position:16% line:89% align:start
with Nagisa in my arms.

00:17:36.229 --> 00:17:38.831 position:16% line:83% align:start
I don't know what I was
doing or where I was going,

00:17:38.831 --> 00:17:40.998 position:10% line:89% align:start
but somehow I ended up here.

00:17:42.899 --> 00:17:45.803 position:7% line:89% align:start
I fell to my knees and prayed.

00:17:45.803 --> 00:17:47.070 position:21% line:89% align:start
Please help Nagisa.

00:17:47.070 --> 00:17:50.339 position:27% line:83% align:start
I don't want her
to die like this.

00:17:50.339 --> 00:17:54.342 position:16% line:83% align:start
That was all I could do.
That was my only hope.

00:17:54.342 --> 00:17:57.378 position:10% line:83% align:start
Then, all of a sudden it was
like the grass and the trees

00:17:57.378 --> 00:18:01.214 position:10% line:83% align:start
and the sun enveloped Nagisa
with this warm light.

00:18:05.183 --> 00:18:08.252 position:30% line:83% align:start
It seemed like
a dream at first...

00:18:08.252 --> 00:18:11.222 position:19% line:83% align:start
but it couldn't be...
it had to be real.

00:18:15.057 --> 00:18:17.059 position:27% line:83% align:start
Tears welled up
in my eyes, and I swear,

00:18:17.059 --> 00:18:20.829 position:10% line:83% align:start
I've never been so grateful
in my entire life.

00:18:20.829 --> 00:18:24.431 position:7% line:83% align:start
Ever since then... I've tried
to keep an eye on this place.

00:18:24.431 --> 00:18:27.634 position:24% line:83% align:start
I almost feel like
it's another part of Nagisa.

00:18:28.901 --> 00:18:30.669 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's a strange story, huh?

00:18:30.669 --> 00:18:32.504 position:21% line:83% align:start
But I'm telling you,
it really happened

00:18:32.504 --> 00:18:33.805 position:27% line:89% align:start
just like that.

00:18:33.805 --> 00:18:36.741 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yeah. I believe you.

00:18:36.741 --> 00:18:39.342 position:16% line:83% align:start
Course that doesn't mean
you can pray and magically have

00:18:39.342 --> 00:18:41.277 position:13% line:89% align:start
all your wishes come true.

00:18:41.277 --> 00:18:43.311 position:21% line:83% align:start
But still... I think
if you push and shove

00:18:43.311 --> 00:18:45.414 position:19% line:83% align:start
with all you got until
the bitter end...

00:18:45.414 --> 00:18:48.850 position:5% line:83% align:start
even if it ain't a miracle, the
results won't be all that bad.

00:18:48.850 --> 00:18:50.284 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yeah, you're probably right.

00:18:50.284 --> 00:18:52.318 position:16% line:83% align:start
Now, I'm not saying she
should have the baby.

00:18:52.318 --> 00:18:55.254 position:5% line:83% align:start
But Nagisa has the most to lose,
so she should decide.

00:18:55.254 --> 00:18:56.555 position:7% line:89% align:start
And whatever her decision is,

00:18:56.555 --> 00:18:58.390 position:19% line:83% align:start
we should all shut up
and accept it.

00:18:58.390 --> 00:19:02.293 position:5% line:89% align:start
Y'know, kid... I mean, Tomoya...

00:19:02.293 --> 00:19:04.261 position:10% line:83% align:start
I hate to say it, but I got
a feeling you got a lot of

00:19:04.261 --> 00:19:06.730 position:19% line:83% align:start
hardship and a lot of
sadness ahead of you.

00:19:06.730 --> 00:19:10.064 position:16% line:83% align:start
But together, you two...
or rather, all of us...

00:19:10.064 --> 00:19:12.567 position:7% line:89% align:start
should be able to overcome it.

00:19:14.335 --> 00:19:15.135 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:19:15.135 --> 00:19:17.204 position:10% line:89% align:start
Remember, we're family, now.

00:19:18.304 --> 00:19:20.673 position:24% line:83% align:start
We're here to help
each other out.

00:19:30.681 --> 00:19:32.215 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa]: I love the breeze.

00:19:32.215 --> 00:19:34.517 position:13% line:89% align:start
It feels so nice and cool.

00:19:36.318 --> 00:19:38.754 position:10% line:89% align:start
[gasps] The baby just moved!

00:19:38.754 --> 00:19:40.488 position:30% line:89% align:start
Whoa, really?!

00:19:42.989 --> 00:19:44.825 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:19:44.825 --> 00:19:47.960 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's a weird feeling, like
it's sliding around in there.

00:19:47.960 --> 00:19:49.562 position:33% line:89% align:start
No kidding?

00:19:55.732 --> 00:19:59.068 position:13% line:83% align:start
Guess we'd better come up
with a name, huh?

00:20:00.536 --> 00:20:02.672 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yeah. I haven't
thought about it much,

00:20:02.672 --> 00:20:05.139 position:16% line:83% align:start
but we need a boys name
and a girls name, don't we?

00:20:05.139 --> 00:20:07.241 position:21% line:83% align:start
Either way, how bout
we take a character

00:20:07.241 --> 00:20:08.476 position:16% line:89% align:start
from your name, Tomoya?

00:20:08.476 --> 00:20:10.811 position:7% line:89% align:start
Nah. It doesn't matter to me.

00:20:10.811 --> 00:20:13.580 position:21% line:83% align:start
Besides, it'll have
my last name either way.

00:20:13.580 --> 00:20:15.781 position:7% line:83% align:start
Let's take something from your
name, instead, how bout that?

00:20:15.781 --> 00:20:18.082 position:19% line:83% align:start
But... my name's kinda
hard to work with,

00:20:18.082 --> 00:20:19.784 position:5% line:89% align:start
so it'll end up sounding silly.

00:20:19.784 --> 00:20:23.520 position:13% line:83% align:start
@Like Nagisako or Nagisami
or something like that.

00:20:23.520 --> 00:20:26.355 position:24% line:83% align:start
Well, okay, Nagisa
means shore, right?

00:20:26.355 --> 00:20:28.858 position:13% line:83% align:start
So how bout we think of a
name that has an ocean theme?

00:20:28.858 --> 00:20:30.758 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, good idea.

00:20:31.793 --> 00:20:34.027 position:13% line:89% align:start
In that case, how bout...

00:20:34.027 --> 00:20:38.097 position:24% line:83% align:start
Ushio. We can use
the character for tide.

00:20:38.097 --> 00:20:39.632 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ushio?

00:20:39.632 --> 00:20:41.767 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yep. Strong and fearless,
the rising and falling

00:20:41.767 --> 00:20:46.170 position:13% line:83% align:start
ocean waves... the endless
ebb and flow of the tide.

00:20:47.938 --> 00:20:49.673 position:27% line:89% align:start
Perfect, right?

00:20:49.673 --> 00:20:52.642 position:13% line:83% align:start
And best of all, it works
whether it's a girl or a boy.

00:20:55.077 --> 00:20:57.178 position:24% line:89% align:start
So it's, Ushio...

00:20:57.178 --> 00:20:58.646 position:30% line:89% align:start
Okazaki, huh?

00:20:58.646 --> 00:21:01.147 position:5% line:83% align:start
@A lot of things happen in life;
Some of them good

00:21:01.147 --> 00:21:03.350 position:16% line:83% align:start
and some of them bad...
but... no matter what,

00:21:03.350 --> 00:21:06.352 position:13% line:77% align:start
@the tide will always come
backúto the shores, again and
again.

00:21:06.352 --> 00:21:07.853 position:19% line:83% align:start
And so, I'll stand by,
watching...

00:21:07.853 --> 00:21:11.956 position:16% line:83% align:start
just as the shores watch
the tide come and go.

00:21:11.956 --> 00:21:13.457 position:27% line:83% align:start
So you're saying
the tides are bigger

00:21:13.457 --> 00:21:16.158 position:10% line:89% align:start
and stronger than the shore?

00:21:16.158 --> 00:21:19.729 position:19% line:83% align:start
Of course. They travel
the whole ocean.

00:21:19.729 --> 00:21:21.129 position:19% line:89% align:start
And like the ocean...

00:21:21.129 --> 00:21:22.864 position:27% line:83% align:start
I hope our child
isn't just strong...

00:21:22.864 --> 00:21:25.866 position:16% line:83% align:start
I hope it's as kind and
nurturing as the deepest waters.

00:21:25.866 --> 00:21:26.834 position:27% line:89% align:start
Don't you agree?

00:21:26.834 --> 00:21:28.568 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yeah, I hope so, too.

00:21:30.803 --> 00:21:33.372 position:19% line:77% align:start
@We couldn't go to the
beachúthis summer after all,
huh?

00:21:33.372 --> 00:21:36.507 position:5% line:89% align:start
I know. It's a shame, isn't it?

00:21:36.507 --> 00:21:39.175 position:19% line:83% align:start
I really wanted to go
to the beach with you.

00:21:39.175 --> 00:21:40.745 position:27% line:83% align:start
All right, then
let's make a promise.

00:21:40.745 --> 00:21:42.812 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa]: A promise?

00:21:42.812 --> 00:21:44.948 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yeah. We're going to come to
the beach with Ushio next year

00:21:44.948 --> 00:21:45.948 position:27% line:89% align:start
no matter what.

00:21:45.948 --> 00:21:47.716 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's a promise.

00:21:47.716 --> 00:21:49.317 position:30% line:89% align:start
A promise...,

00:21:53.387 --> 00:21:56.455 position:21% line:83% align:start
Uh-huh. You promise,
right... Nagisa?

00:21:58.457 --> 00:22:01.526 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, of course. I promise...

00:23:43.636 --> 00:23:46.071 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Kotomi]: I've been talking
about one Hidden World,

00:23:46.071 --> 00:23:49.172 position:10% line:83% align:start
but there may be any number
of them out there.

00:23:49.172 --> 00:23:51.375 position:19% line:83% align:start
In fact, there may be
as many worlds

00:23:51.375 --> 00:23:53.710 position:13% line:83% align:start
as there are possibilities
in our lives.

00:23:53.710 --> 00:23:56.946 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Tomoya]: Fujibayashi, you said
something like that a long time
ago

00:23:56.946 --> 00:23:59.081 position:19% line:83% align:start
when you were telling
our fortunes, right?

00:23:59.081 --> 00:24:01.916 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Ryou]: Right. The future
isn't something predetermined,

00:24:01.916 --> 00:24:04.551 position:19% line:83% align:start
there are all sorts of
possibilities out there.

00:24:04.551 --> 00:24:06.919 position:19% line:89% align:start
I still believe that.

